Gary Ballance scored 122 in England's first innings of the first Test against West Indies at the Sir Vivian Richards Stadium in Antigua . 
  Joe Root and Jos Buttler added 114 for the second wicket . 
  Chris Jordan took the wickets of Darren Bravo and Kraigg Brathwaite . 
  England set West Indies a target of 438 in their first innings . 
  West Indies are 98 for two at the end of day four of the Test . 
 